11:25.284 --> 11:27.224
cost more than your
private school tuition,

11:27.294 --> 11:28.755
you little bitch.

11:31.018 --> 11:33.263
So, Brooke, what's your deal?

11:33.403 --> 11:36.428
Okay, quick intros. Eric, story monster.

11:36.497 --> 11:38.334
Lyle, his brother, is a joke beast.

11:38.655 --> 11:41.076
We got Izzy and Taz from "The
Pickup Artist" community,

11:41.145 --> 11:43.356
Brian from Harvard, our
YouTube sensation.

11:43.381 --> 11:44.724
Demios of Chaldes,

11:44.785 --> 11:46.830
and Julie, who is a woman.

11:46.878 --> 11:49.709
And a... "story machine."
But can she take a joke?

11:49.787 --> 11:51.874
Or are you one of those
uptight feminists?

11:52.000 --> 11:54.086
Oh, no, I hate women.

11:54.267 --> 11:57.107
I got into TV writing so I
could <i>not</i> write for them.

11:57.161 --> 11:59.581
Fuck, yeah! Oh, did you
hear Drew Barrymore

11:59.637 --> 12:01.473
on "Howard Stern" this morning? I did.

12:01.521 --> 12:03.161
- She got old, right?
- [SOMEONE CHUCKLES]

12:03.185 --> 12:05.617
She's a dog now. She used to be a 9.

12:05.712 --> 12:07.795
Yeah, when she was 9!

12:07.868 --> 12:09.829
[FORCED LAUGH] Right?

12:10.228 --> 12:12.396
Somebody should slit her... throat

12:12.496 --> 12:14.876
and make a lampshade out of her skin.

12:16.912 --> 12:18.474
Baba Booey?

12:18.693 --> 12:21.295
'Kay, let's blue sky this bitch!

12:21.445 --> 12:23.825
Who has got ideas

12:23.905 --> 12:25.912
for "Panda's Birthday Party"?

12:25.998 --> 12:28.763
What if, uh, Panda took
Kitten to the party

12:28.821 --> 12:30.657
and everybody liked Kitten more?

12:30.783 --> 12:33.120
No. That's not very good.

12:33.723 --> 12:35.060
You have another pitch?

12:35.146 --> 12:37.347
Hmm? Oh, no.

12:37.512 --> 12:39.557
I-I just didn't like that.

12:39.784 --> 12:42.631
Well, okay, what if,
uh, Kitten's birthday

12:42.718 --> 12:44.256
is the same day as Panda's?

12:44.335 --> 12:46.840
And Kitten is jealous

12:47.075 --> 12:48.740
of all of the attention

12:48.807 --> 12:49.928
that Panda's getting?

12:49.957 --> 12:51.998
Yeah, jealousy. It's real.

12:52.076 --> 12:54.412
My pig wife said no to a threesome

12:54.468 --> 12:56.188
with our cleaning lady
because of jealousy.

12:56.212 --> 12:58.287
Ohh... I'm so sorry.

12:58.543 --> 13:00.089
Yeah.

13:01.242 --> 13:05.040
Or... what if we don't do
anything about a birthday party

13:05.065 --> 13:07.560
and the gang starts a food truck?

13:08.300 --> 13:10.303
How does that fit into
the story diamond?

13:10.679 --> 13:12.307
- The what?
- You're a story machine,

13:12.355 --> 13:14.075
and you don't know about
the story diamond?

13:14.123 --> 13:15.963
- That's Kenny's thing.
- Yeah. Talked about it

13:15.987 --> 13:17.477
on "Marc Maron" for 3 1/2 hours

13:17.532 --> 13:20.328
after my mom's stuff and
his vinyl collection.

13:20.360 --> 13:21.880
Yeah, yeah, you take a diamond, right?

13:21.927 --> 13:24.515
You split it in half, then
you cut it in 16 segments.

13:24.946 --> 13:26.818
And on the left you
got your plot points,

13:26.863 --> 13:28.657
and then you cross-correspond that

13:28.712 --> 13:30.201
to the segments on the right

13:30.263 --> 13:32.224
where you got your characters in crises.

13:32.419 --> 13:33.559
Story diamond.

13:33.598 --> 13:35.037
Obviously, I'm familiar with it,

13:35.101 --> 13:37.772
but Neil, you know, my old boss,

13:38.102 --> 13:40.084
um, didn't like to do that.

13:40.179 --> 13:41.966
He preferred the way I break a story.

13:42.058 --> 13:44.052
We could call Neil and ask him but...

13:44.317 --> 13:46.695
he's in that coma, so...

13:47.318 --> 13:48.584
Lunch?

13:48.655 --> 13:50.283
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:50.331 --> 13:52.263
I just received four pages of notes

13:52.297 --> 13:54.885
from my mom on a 1/2
page bat mitzvah toast.

13:54.988 --> 13:56.508
Well, if it makes you feel any better,

13:56.532 --> 14:00.470
Mickey Dolenz's one-man show
has an 87-page cold open.

14:00.646 --> 14:02.732
That stupid dream board came true,

14:02.765 --> 14:04.645
and it turns out working
with my childhood idol

14:04.669 --> 14:05.987
is a fucking nightmare! Yeah.

14:06.043 --> 14:07.880
And my dream of writing for TV

14:07.952 --> 14:10.080
turns out to be men incapable
of talking to women

14:10.127 --> 14:12.047
telling me I don't know
how women actually talk!

14:12.117 --> 14:13.787
Hello, last looks.

14:13.945 --> 14:15.427
Uh-oh.

14:15.542 --> 14:17.326
Cake buffet?

14:17.548 --> 14:19.388
Either your first day
of work went poorly,

14:19.445 --> 14:21.281
or Pete Holmes got another break.

14:21.407 --> 14:23.810
I am picking out a cake for
my mother's bat mitzvah.

14:23.888 --> 14:25.528
And technically, yes,
I already chose one

14:25.552 --> 14:27.123
when I went to the bakery with Billy.

14:27.197 --> 14:29.437
I just need to make sure that
I made the right decision.

14:29.461 --> 14:31.716
- So work went okay.
- Absolutely not!

14:31.875 --> 14:33.451
Did you know that TV writing

14:33.488 --> 14:35.728
is just people stuck in a room
together talking all day?

14:35.791 --> 14:38.191
It's like a cocktail party with
the ugliest people on earth.

14:38.245 --> 14:39.993
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:40.393 --> 14:41.943
You're just gonna split

14:42.056 --> 14:43.825
- a side of Brussels sprouts...
- Billy!

14:43.885 --> 14:46.347
- Quick question.
- Mickey, I'm at work.

14:46.496 --> 14:48.045
And your questions are rarely quick.

14:48.114 --> 14:49.741
I'll be right back. Thank you.

14:49.813 --> 14:51.396
Mickey Dolenz.

14:51.577 --> 14:53.372
You said you had some notes for me

14:53.429 --> 14:56.826
- on the Roddy McDowall duet.
- Oh, not notes.

14:56.902 --> 14:58.482
Uh, questions, actually.

14:58.545 --> 15:01.257
Specifically what, how, and why?

15:01.413 --> 15:03.857
Pretty straight forward.
Um, I'm singing,

15:03.897 --> 15:06.400
"Hey, Hey, We're the Monkees,"
with Roddy McDowall,

15:06.479 --> 15:08.982
who's dressed as Cornelius
from "Planet of the Apes."

15:09.091 --> 15:11.295
Did you know that Roddy
McDowall is dead?

15:11.455 --> 15:12.521
Which is why

15:12.585 --> 15:15.465
we're gonna use a hologram, obviously.

15:15.528 --> 15:17.435
Even if you could afford the technology

15:17.488 --> 15:19.138
that would make that dream a reality,

15:19.211 --> 15:20.826
do you have any footage anywhere

15:20.883 --> 15:23.164
of Roddy McDowall singing,
"Hey, Hey, We're the Monkees"?

15:23.188 --> 15:25.023
- Because, if not...
- I see, yeah.

15:25.520 --> 15:28.623
Smart. Let me noodle on that.

15:28.811 --> 15:31.774
Meanwhile, I've added a new song.

15:31.954 --> 15:34.287
- [PAPER SLAPS DOWN]
- Mickey, I'm sorry, I'm done.

15:34.410 --> 15:35.802
Billy, I'm dyin'.

15:35.900 --> 15:38.070
No offense, Mickey, but... when?

15:38.266 --> 15:40.138
Billy, you said in your letter...

15:40.218 --> 15:42.591
I wrote that same fan letter
to Olivia Newton John.

15:42.651 --> 15:44.302
I was a child. And by the way,

15:44.370 --> 15:46.090
her turnaround was a
lot faster than yours.

15:46.114 --> 15:48.135
She sent me a "Xanadu" head
shot in, like, a week.

15:48.321 --> 15:51.443
Well... I guess this is good-bye.

15:51.663 --> 15:53.123
Yeah.

15:53.241 --> 15:54.724
I'll see you in another 30 years.

15:54.803 --> 15:56.717
No, Billy.

15:57.489 --> 15:59.295
You won't.

16:02.298 --> 16:04.521
Mickey Dolenz. I'm dying!

16:04.563 --> 16:08.154
Now, Marilyn, your Torah
portion will be Tehillim.

16:08.280 --> 16:10.868
"Delight in God, and he will give thee

16:10.971 --> 16:12.807
the desires of thy heart."

16:13.245 --> 16:16.810
It means... believe in your daydreams.

16:17.246 --> 16:19.040
Be a Daydream Believer.

16:19.173 --> 16:22.430
Or Daydream Belieber. Right, girls?

16:23.333 --> 16:25.044
Justin Bieber?

16:25.560 --> 16:27.552
We love him, right?

16:27.884 --> 16:30.889
Yeah. Because he's so cool.

16:30.961 --> 16:34.459
Okay, I was born without the
ability to sense sarcasm,

16:34.587 --> 16:38.135
so I'm just gonna keep pitching
and see what you might like.

16:38.293 --> 16:40.463
Okay, wait a minute. This might be cool.

16:40.800 --> 16:42.732
Do you like chicken?

16:43.393 --> 16:45.063
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSICAL STING]</i>

16:45.126 --> 16:46.670
Okay, let's break this.

16:46.749 --> 16:48.060
Panda's birthday story

16:48.110 --> 16:49.724
like it was a virgin's hymen.

16:49.873 --> 16:52.310
[SOMEONE PUFFING RAPIDLY]

16:53.015 --> 16:55.019
<i>[DRAMATIC STING]</i>

16:56.789 --> 17:00.021
God. "Panda's Party" is <i>not</i> tracking!

17:00.752 --> 17:02.462
Oh, my God.

17:02.636 --> 17:04.638
<i>[DRAMATIC STING]</i>

17:04.715 --> 17:06.248
Is Kenny still on that phone call?

17:06.296 --> 17:07.672
It's been like an hour!

17:07.853 --> 17:09.551
Well, it's his divorce lawyer,

17:09.596 --> 17:11.029
so you never know.

17:11.106 --> 17:13.233
But he doesn't let us work without him.

17:13.375 --> 17:14.501
Ugh!

17:14.540 --> 17:16.021
<i>[DRAMATIC STING]</i>

17:16.233 --> 17:17.873
Fuck. My ex.

17:17.965 --> 17:19.459
I fuckin' hate women, Kenny.

17:19.534 --> 17:20.637
Let's fix this Panda story.

17:20.671 --> 17:22.482
Everybody order dinner.

17:22.550 --> 17:23.982
It's gonna be a late night.

17:24.378 --> 17:26.339
<i>[DRAMATIC STING]</i>

17:26.521 --> 17:29.193
Well, she got all the Criterion DVDs

17:29.256 --> 17:30.404
and the gun cabinet,

17:30.434 --> 17:33.466
but one upside to losing
everything to that bitch

17:33.567 --> 17:36.197
is I don't have to stay sober anymore!

17:36.362 --> 17:38.657
So, wait, because Kenny's
going through a divorce,

17:38.806 --> 17:40.466
we have to stay here all night?

17:40.648 --> 17:41.723
Yeah.

17:42.152 --> 17:43.763
Isn't there, like, a writer's union

17:43.825 --> 17:45.305
to protect us from that kind of shit?

17:45.329 --> 17:46.997
[LAUGHTER]

17:47.199 --> 17:49.035
Finally, she says something funny.

17:49.357 --> 17:51.361
<i>[DRAMATIC STING]</i>

17:52.402 --> 17:54.834
Ah, God, come on, you fuckers, think!

17:54.889 --> 17:58.341
All right? Panda Kitten, Sunflower,

17:58.421 --> 18:00.842
ad Panda has a birthday!

18:01.211 --> 18:02.545
Bamboo-eating cocksucker!

18:02.609 --> 18:04.896
Okay, what if, uh,

18:05.044 --> 18:07.590
Panda has a surprise birthday party

18:08.044 --> 18:09.750
but no one shows up.

18:09.836 --> 18:11.211
So nothing happens?

18:11.294 --> 18:13.130
How's that fit into
Kenny's story diamond?

18:13.334 --> 18:14.934
What'd I tell you about women and story?

18:14.994 --> 18:16.872
Okay, fuck you, Brian!

18:17.006 --> 18:18.465
Because what I just pitched

18:18.513 --> 18:19.664
fits perfectly

18:19.720 --> 18:22.992
into the story... double helix

18:23.227 --> 18:24.906
that me and Neil came up with

18:24.941 --> 18:27.203
when we were working on that
Gina Gershon show together.

18:27.252 --> 18:28.880
- "Dumb Whore"?
- Double helix?

18:28.944 --> 18:31.280
Yeah. Neil said it was bulletproof

18:31.414 --> 18:33.709
and totally next level, but I understand

18:33.757 --> 18:36.047
if you guys wanna play it
safe with the diamond.

18:36.112 --> 18:38.594
No, explain the double helix, all right?

18:38.684 --> 18:40.625
Just draw it up there. Explain it to us.

18:40.698 --> 18:42.062
- Right now?
- Walk us through it!

18:42.134 --> 18:43.367
Do what Kenny says!

18:43.412 --> 18:45.101
- Yes, go, go, go, go, go.
- Okay.

18:45.202 --> 18:47.765
All right, well, okay, so
the story double helix...

18:47.845 --> 18:49.571
- Yeah, yeah, yeah, just draw it.
- Here's the first helix,

18:49.595 --> 18:50.915
- right?
- Yeah, boom, boom, boom.

18:50.939 --> 18:54.743
And, you know, like any, uh,
organism, it has quadrants.

18:54.800 --> 18:59.125
So there are 56 quadrants
in each subset.

18:59.150 --> 19:01.150
- Let's get some more Thai food.
- How many noodles

19:01.175 --> 19:02.735
- do you need?
- Noodles are brain food.

19:02.759 --> 19:03.927
No, they're not!

19:04.038 --> 19:05.679
<i>[DRAMATIC STING]</i>

19:05.909 --> 19:08.859
Now the hero has refused

19:08.932 --> 19:09.984
the journey,

19:10.034 --> 19:11.912
but that's when we get

19:11.992 --> 19:13.304
the four alligators,

19:13.329 --> 19:16.084
which I call internal conflicts.

19:16.145 --> 19:18.816
- I'm confused.
- Oh, are you confused, Brian?

19:18.989 --> 19:20.367
It's so simple!

19:20.413 --> 19:22.458
And it applies to any movie.

19:22.522 --> 19:25.461
My God, if Neil were here,
he would laugh at you.

19:25.526 --> 19:26.861
If Neil were where?

19:27.261 --> 19:29.148
Hey! Oh ho ho!

19:29.215 --> 19:31.344
Neil, you're outta your coma!

19:31.392 --> 19:34.359
Yeah, I got out yesterday.
First thing I wanted to do

19:34.449 --> 19:35.562
was come back to work

19:35.641 --> 19:38.187
because I have a horrible marriage.

19:38.844 --> 19:41.726
Well, your story machine

19:41.851 --> 19:44.101
is explaining your double helix to us.

19:44.505 --> 19:45.640
Who the fuck are you

19:45.702 --> 19:48.248
and what the fuck is a double helix?

19:50.042 --> 19:52.703
Julie... you're a good fuck...

19:52.783 --> 19:53.906
Aw...

19:54.022 --> 19:56.401
But you are a shitty story machine.

19:56.622 --> 19:59.044
So... you are fired.

20:00.537 --> 20:01.997
Well, fine.

20:02.193 --> 20:04.446
Because... I quit anyway.

20:04.744 --> 20:06.497
And you know what else?

20:06.789 --> 20:09.226
None you have any point of view

20:09.282 --> 20:11.672
formed outside your own shitty lives.

20:11.723 --> 20:13.475
You guys are bad writers.

20:13.562 --> 20:16.750
Not <i>just</i> because you lack imagination,

20:17.384 --> 20:19.472
but because you lack empathy.

20:21.366 --> 20:23.320
So suck... my... fat...

20:23.391 --> 20:25.228
a-twat!

20:27.204 --> 20:29.541
Jeez. It's your own fault.

20:30.081 --> 20:31.617
For hiring a woman.

20:31.738 --> 20:32.948
Ha ha!

20:33.043 --> 20:34.336
Neil!

20:34.383 --> 20:35.515
All those dream boards did

20:35.570 --> 20:37.851
was give us what we want after
we didn't want it anymore,

20:37.920 --> 20:39.094
Like Calista Flockhart

20:39.152 --> 20:40.872
when Harrison Ford
finally called her back.

20:41.044 --> 20:42.563
And now that I think about
it, I'm pretty sure

20:42.587 --> 20:44.227
I was working with the
Menendez brothers.

20:44.278 --> 20:45.696
But on the bright side,

20:45.751 --> 20:47.781
they still had to pay
me for the whole week.

20:47.860 --> 20:50.113
Look. Check it out.

20:50.317 --> 20:53.219
Whoa! Oh, my God!

20:53.601 --> 20:55.768
If this is what giving notes to
Mickey Dolenz would have paid,

20:55.792 --> 20:57.752
I never would have quit.
Do you know that he came

20:57.776 --> 20:59.656
and dropped off a song for the ending

20:59.725 --> 21:01.937
- even after I bailed?
- Aw!

21:02.422 --> 21:05.070
"Number One Fan."

21:05.386 --> 21:07.062
Holy shit, Billy. This is about you.

21:07.156 --> 21:08.351
- What?
- Yeah, he's saying

21:08.376 --> 21:09.576
that he's your number one fan.

21:09.640 --> 21:10.742
- Look!
- No.

21:10.852 --> 21:12.122
Yeah!

21:12.707 --> 21:14.008
Oh, my God!

21:14.062 --> 21:16.524
He even talks about my curly hair!

21:16.611 --> 21:17.710
Fuck!

21:17.840 --> 21:19.550
Now I can't quit on him!

21:19.591 --> 21:21.887
I'm gonna go find him. I
mean, I have no problem

21:21.966 --> 21:23.265
walking away from a dying man,

21:23.290 --> 21:25.252
but I can't walk away from a dying <i>fan.</i>

21:25.312 --> 21:27.328
I'll see you at Marilyn's bat mitzvah?

21:28.414 --> 21:31.117
Ooh! A Jewish birthday party.

21:31.232 --> 21:33.610
Who will I bring? What will I wear?

21:33.760 --> 21:34.945
Oh, fuck!

21:35.006 --> 21:37.593
Fuck, fuck, fuck, fuck, fuck!

21:37.688 --> 21:40.078
Uh, that's what she said! [GIGGLING]

21:40.371 --> 21:42.411
I forgot to send out those
bat mitzvah invitations!

21:42.452 --> 21:43.859
Now no one's gonna come!

21:43.938 --> 21:45.606
That's what <i>he</i> said!

21:45.685 --> 21:47.958
[LAUGHING]

21:50.559 --> 21:53.312
[LAUGHS LOUDER]

21:56.948 --> 21:58.324
[GLASSES CLATTERING]

21:58.403 --> 21:59.906
Hey, how's my favorite client,

21:59.985 --> 22:01.742
aka, the back of Reba McEntire's head

22:01.817 --> 22:04.237
in a Hallmark movie if you're
available on Thursday.

22:04.411 --> 22:06.328
I am completely available on Thursday,

22:06.367 --> 22:07.492
but I wanted to know

22:07.517 --> 22:10.140
if you could fill a
synagogue in three hours.

22:10.542 --> 22:12.587
How many stand-ins will this get me?

22:13.602 --> 22:15.145
Mom! There you are.

22:15.520 --> 22:17.953
I was looking for you. Don't cry!

22:18.147 --> 22:20.179
No one's here, Julie.

22:20.280 --> 22:21.922
I texted Bonnie, and she said

22:21.972 --> 22:24.203
she never even got an invitation.

22:24.255 --> 22:26.455
I didn't invite Bonnie. Why
would we want Bonnie here?

22:26.503 --> 22:28.328
We hate Bonnie! Don't worry.

22:28.353 --> 22:30.230
I promise, the synagogue will be full.

22:30.285 --> 22:32.781
Maybe not with the same
attendees that we'd hoped,

22:32.851 --> 22:36.316
but does your Romanian
hairdresser always say?

22:36.723 --> 22:38.308
[WITH ACCENT] "Don't worry."

22:38.575 --> 22:42.206
Warts aren't contagious. Cash only!"

22:42.355 --> 22:44.395
Okay, well, I was gonna say
"volume is everything,"

22:44.423 --> 22:46.992
- but kudos on that impression.
- Well, thank you.

22:47.083 --> 22:48.740
It'll be great. I promise.

22:48.820 --> 22:50.349
Billy even brought a celebrity.

22:50.418 --> 22:52.357
It better not be Marcia Gay Harden.

22:52.427 --> 22:55.943
She owes me $1,200, and she knows why!

22:55.988 --> 22:58.591
Julie, cheer me up. Read my toast.

22:58.834 --> 23:00.587
Okay.

23:02.118 --> 23:04.560
All right, here it is.

23:05.063 --> 23:06.941
[EXHALES] "To Marilyn",

23:07.020 --> 23:09.982
"who waited her whole life
for a perfect bat mitzvah.

23:10.425 --> 23:12.896
"But I learned a lesson
from a panda recently.

23:13.324 --> 23:16.325
"A party is perfect when you're
around people who love you.

23:16.624 --> 23:18.167
The rest is just cake."

23:18.855 --> 23:20.630
- It's lovely.
- Thanks.

23:20.738 --> 23:22.866
It's based on something
called the story diamond,

23:23.047 --> 23:24.967
which, turns out, really does work.

23:26.789 --> 23:29.251
Mickey, I'm really sorry
I walked out on you.

23:29.378 --> 23:31.622
We're cool. And thanks for inviting me

23:31.687 --> 23:33.786
to this older lady's 12 birthday party.

23:33.874 --> 23:36.503
Now, our bat mitzvah
girl, Marilyn Kessler,

23:36.692 --> 23:39.113
will read from the Torah.

23:44.734 --> 23:47.825
[MARILYN CHANTING]

23:47.900 --> 23:49.779
Billy, are you sure
this Budapest tour...

23:49.854 --> 23:52.365
- Shh! Mickey, she's reading.
- Shh!

23:52.600 --> 23:54.729
Mickey Dolenz?

23:54.870 --> 23:55.955
Uh-oh.

